BILLSCAN PHONE NEGOTIATION SCRIPT
Bill: {{facilityName}} | Total: ${{totalBilled}} | Savings Target: ${{totalSavings}}

STEP 1 — CALL BILLING DEPARTMENT
"Hi, I'm calling about my recent bill from {{facilityName}}, statement date {{statementDate}}. I have some questions about specific charges."

STEP 2 — REQUEST ITEMIZED BILL (if you don't have one)
"Can you send me a fully itemized bill with CPT codes for each charge? I'm entitled to this under federal law."

STEP 3 — CHALLENGE SPECIFIC CHARGES (start with biggest)
{{#each topFindings}}
"I see a charge of ${{this.billedAmount}} for {{this.description}} (CPT {{this.cptCode}}). The Medicare rate for this procedure is ${{this.cmsRateUsed}}. That's a {{this.overchargeMultiplier}}x markup. Can you explain why this charge is so much higher?"
{{/each}}

STEP 4 — ASK FOR REDUCTION
"Based on my research, the CMS baseline for all these services totals ${{totalCmsBaseline}}. I understand hospitals charge more than Medicare, but ${{totalBilled}} is {{averageMultiplier}}x the baseline. I'd like to discuss a fair adjustment."

STEP 5 — ESCALATE IF NEEDED
"I'd like to speak with a billing supervisor or patient advocate, please."
"I'm prepared to file a formal dispute and have documentation from the CMS fee schedule."

STEP 6 — ASK ABOUT ASSISTANCE
"Do you have a financial assistance or charity care program I can apply for?"
"What is your self-pay discount rate?"

NOTES:
- Stay calm and polite — you have leverage with data
- Take names and reference numbers for every call
- Follow up in writing within 48 hours
- Report ID: {{reportId}} (for your records)
